snippet.title: Outlander | The Final Season: Official Trailer | STARZ
snippet.description:
The global phenomenon returns for its final farewell and you won’t want to miss a single moment. Outlander’s eighth and final season premieres March 6 only on STARZ.

Song: "A Dawning" by Ólafur Arnalds & Talos 

#STARZ #Outlander 

Watch Outlander now on the STARZ app: http://starz.tv/WatchSTARZYT

Subscribe now for more Outlander content: http://bit.ly/1kalhP0 

Like Outlander on Facebook: http://starz.tv/OutlanderFacebookYT
Follow Outlander on Instagram: http://starz.tv/OutlanderInstagramYT

Outlander is internationally distributed by Sony Pictures Television.

Facebook: http://starz.tv/STARZFacebookYT
Instagram: http://starz.tv/STARZInstagramYT
YouTube: https://starz.tv/STARZYouTube
TikTok: https://starz.tv/STARZTikTokYT

Outlander Season 7 ended with Jamie’s fateful decision to resign his Continental Army commission and return to Fraser’s Ridge with Claire. Meanwhile, after an emotional family reunion, the MacKenzies needed to decide where and when to settle next, and a haunting cliffhanger left fans questioning the true fate of Claire and Jamie’s first daughter, Faith.

As Season 8 begins, Jamie and Claire soon find the war has followed them home to Fraser’s Ridge, now a thriving settlement that has grown and flourished in their absence. With new arrivals and changes made during their years away, the Frasers are confronted with the question of what they are willing to sacrifice for the place they call home and, more importantly, what they would sacrifice to stay together. While the Frasers keep a united front against outside intruders, family secrets finally coming to light threaten to tear them apart from the inside. Although they’ve left the war for America’s freedom behind, their fight for Fraser’s Ridge has only just begun.

Outlander stars Caitríona Balfe as Claire Fraser, Sam Heughan as Jamie Fraser, Sophie Skelton as Brianna MacKenzie, Richard Rankin as Roger MacKenzie, John Bell as Young Ian Murray, David Berry as Lord John Grey, Charles Vandervaart as William Ransom, Izzy Meikle-Small as Rachel Murray, Lauren Lyle as Marsali Fraser and César Domboy as Fergus Fraser.

snippet.title: Highlander - First Trailer (2026) Henry Cavill, Russell Crowe, Dave Bautista | Amazon MGM Studios
snippet.description:
— Attention Viewers ⚠️
— This is a Fan-Made Concept Trailer for:
— Highlander

— This video is a fan-made concept trailer, created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes.The goal behind this trailer is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through a concept trailer based on a unique and original idea. By combining various effects, sound design, and AI technologies, I’ve crafted a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support — now let’s dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. 🎬✨

— In this concept trailer for Highlander, the story follows Connor MacLeod, portrayed by Henry Cavill, an immortal warrior burdened by centuries of survival and loss, now living quietly in modern-day New York as the past closes in around him. Trained long ago by his mentor Juan Sánchez-Villalobos Ramírez, played by Russell Crowe, Connor is drawn back into an ancient conflict as the Gathering approaches and his oldest enemy, the brutal Kurgan, portrayed by Dave Bautista, resurfaces to finish a war that has never truly ended. As immortals once again move toward an inevitable confrontation where only one can remain, Connor is forced to reckon with the cost of endless life, the weight of unfinished history, and the question of whether endurance alone is enough when destiny demands a final stand.

snippet.title: Motionless In White - Afraid of the Dark [Official Video]
snippet.description:
The Official Music Video for Motionless In White's new single "Afraid of the Dark" available everywhere now on Roadrunner Records

Stream “Afraid of the Dark” 
https://miw.lnk.to/afraidofthedark

The Afraid Of The Dark Tour in the UK and Europe begins February 5th - Get your tickets now: https://www.motionlessinwhite.net/tour

Produced by Justin deBlieck & WZRDBLD
Mixed and mastered by Zakk Cervini

Directed, Edited, VFX - Max Moore
Executive Producers - DJay Brawner, Max Rose
Producers - Zach Miners, Marc Singer
Director of Photography, additional VFX - Andrew Robinson
1st AC - Kennedy Cochran
Gaffer - Zachary Erwin
Grip - Daniel Williamson 
Electric - John Ricketts 
Set Design / Construction - Rob Gagnon & Jason Rubino
Set Construction - Shelby Conquest
Scenic - Liz Wolf
Production Design - Sally Wegert
Makeup (Chris) - Laura Lomonaco 
Makeup (Band) - Trevor Thompson
Makeup concept (Chris look 1) Katelyn Droegemeier
Wardrobe provided by Killstar 
Additional VFX (debris) - Joey Deutsch
PA - Eric Spurgeon
Color - Post 237, Duncan Salot
Asset Rendering - Ken Lutz 
BTS - Acacia Evans, Andy Nice
Management - Kim Schon, Macy Gilbert
Commissioner - Chris Brown
Production Company - Tuff 

Follow MIW
https://www.motionlessinwhite.net
https://www.instagram.com/motionlessinwhite
https://twitter.com/miwband
https://tiktok.com/@motionlessinwhite

LYRICS

I‘ve given my life
I suffered and sacrificed to find
That fear is only fatal till it’s alchemized
To heal is to repurpose
Take the stage and siphon all the power from the pain 
I turned my struggles into my strength

If the answer is in the unknown
Would you question the path you take?
If the past didn’t hurt to let go
Would your future be yours to reclaim?

You’ll never know 
Yourself till you walk alone
With blind faith and broken bones
So follow the light in your heart, and be not afraid of the dark 

Will you follow me to where love met destruction?
Doubt only dies if you keep pouring trust in
Fight or surrender your dreams
Cause it’s give up or give everything 

You’ll never know 
Yourself till you walk alone
With blind faith and broken bones
So carry the torch in your heart, and be not afraid of the dark 

How much are you willing to bleed,
To suffer for what you believe?
We can’t see the end from the start, so don’t be afraid of the dark 
And walk with me

From the ashes I was reborn free
And from the grave I was rebuilt by what broke me  

So tear me apart and you’ll see 
You’ll see the spine, the heart, the blood on the dirt 
You’ll feel the pain, the rage that feeds on the hurt 
On every scar is a badge of a lesson i’ve learned 
That took me twenty fucking years to earn 

And now I know
I don’t have to do this alone 
A creature that found a home 
When life drained the light from my heart, you pulled me from the dark 

I’ve given you everything
A lifeline in pieces of me
We can’t see the end from the start, but I don’t fear the dark  

Dark Inside, with purpose and passion
Sweat and blood, from Stockholm to Scranton 
Fight or fright, arise from the pages 
Fear not the dark, if you mean it you’ll make it 

#motionlessinwhite #MIW #AfraidoftheDark

snippet.title: ERRA - further eden (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
“further eden” by @ERRAband is out now. New album ‘silence outlives the earth’ out March 6.

Order/save at https://erra.lnk.to/silence


slow delusion is demanding 
of repeated histories  
I will die inside the lines of
countless thousand other dreams 
further down below
I’m swimming through the static
growing cynical
and the edge is symptomatic 
through the panic I find my peace
dive slow
shatter into the sun 
too close
pressure I can’t outrun 
and I know I can’t be the only one 
drowning 
how far can we sink into the abyss 
face yourself for once
I’m averse to acquiescence 
to a digital time leech  
losing ground in keeping essence 
with our spirits being breached 
how much love is lost 
when the rush is automatic 
when you mime along 
and the notes all ring chromatic 
through the panic I find my peace
on the other side 
of the pact I made with grief 
dive slow
shatter into the sun 
too close  
pressure I can’t outrun 
and I know I can’t be the only one 
drowning 
how far can we sink into the abyss 
face yourself for once 
the bar is dropping lower 
and the air is growing thinner 
we’re on the wrong side of the surface
and we’re going under 
we’re on the wrong side of a loaded gun
we’ll freeze beneath an indifferent sun
face yourself 
face yourself for once
